# Axiora Project Rules and Patterns

## Code Organization
1. File Structure
   - Core functionality in root directory
   - UI components in uiEXT/
   - Modules in modules/
   - Tests in test/
   - Resources in resources/

2. Naming Conventions
   - Classes: PascalCase
   - Functions: snake_case
   - Variables: snake_case
   - Constants: UPPER_CASE
   - Private members: _prefix

3. Import Order
   - Standard library imports
   - Third-party imports
   - Local application imports

## Development Workflow
1. Version Control
   - Feature branches
   - Pull requests
   - Commit messages
   - Code review

2. Testing
   - Unit tests for core functionality
   - UI tests for components
   - Data validation tests
   - Performance tests

3. Documentation
   - Docstrings for all functions
   - Module-level documentation
   - API documentation
   - User guides

## UI/UX Patterns
1. Layout
   - Responsive design
   - Consistent spacing
   - Clear hierarchy
   - Intuitive navigation

2. Components
   - Reusable widgets
   - Consistent styling
   - Clear feedback
   - Error handling

3. Theming
   - Dark/light modes
   - Custom themes
   - Consistent colors
   - Accessible design

## Data Management
1. Database
   - SQLite for local storage
   - Structured schemas
   - Efficient queries
   - Data validation

2. Analysis
   - Clean data processing
   - Efficient algorithms
   - Clear visualization
   - Accurate reporting

3. Security
   - Secure authentication
   - Data encryption
   - Access control
   - Audit logging

## Performance Guidelines
1. Optimization
   - Efficient algorithms
   - Memory management
   - Caching strategies
   - Lazy loading

2. UI Performance
   - Responsive updates
   - Efficient rendering
   - Background processing
   - Progress indicators

3. Data Handling
   - Batch processing
   - Streaming support
   - Compression
   - Caching

## Error Handling
1. User Errors
   - Clear messages
   - Recovery options
   - Helpful suggestions
   - Logging

2. System Errors
   - Graceful degradation
   - Error recovery
   - System logging
   - User notification

3. Data Errors
   - Validation
   - Correction
   - Reporting
   - Prevention 